        },
        {
          "@id": "pkg:oci/kube-scheduler?repository_url=ghcr.io/oleksandr-minakov/lts-k8s-opus48"
        },
        {
          "@id": "pkg:oci/kube-proxy?repository_url=ghcr.io/oleksandr-minakov/lts-k8s-opus48"
        },
        {
          "@id": "pkg:deb/kubelet"
        }
      ],
      "status": "affected",
      "action_statement": "Deferred on the 1.32 LTS line. The fix (go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk >= 1.40) transitively pulls github.com/cyphar/filepath-securejoin v0.6.0, which removes the top-level MkdirAllHandle that vendored runc v1.2.1 requires, breaking the build. Exploitation requires OpenTelemetry tracing to be explicitly enabled (off by default) AND adversary control of the process PATH. Mitigate by leaving tracing disabled and not running components with an attacker-influenced PATH. Will be fixed when the LTS line moves to a runc release compatible with the new securejoin API."
    },
    {
      "vulnerability": {
        "name": "CVE-2025-52881",
        "aliases": [
          "GO-2025-4098"
        ]
      },
      "products": [
        {
          "@id": "pkg:oci/kube-apiserver?repository_url=ghcr.io/oleksandr-minakov/lts-k8s-opus48"
        },
        {
          "@id": "pkg:oci/kube-controller-manager?repository_url=ghcr.io/oleksandr-minakov/lts-k8s-opus48"
        },
        {
          "@id": "pkg:oci/kube-proxy?repository_url=ghcr.io/oleksandr-minakov/lts-k8s-opus48"
        },
        {
          "@id": "pkg:deb/kubelet"
        }
      ],
      "status": "not_affected",
      "justification": "vulnerable_code_not_in_execute_path",
      "impact_statement": "This is a container-escape via procfs write redirection that occurs in the runc that actually creates containers. Kubernetes components vendor opencontainers/runc and selinux only for label/constant computation; they do not spawn containers from the vendored copy \u2014 the node's container runtime (containerd/CRI-O + its own runc) is the affected component and is patched independently at the node level. govulncheck flags the shared symbol as present, but the container-creation path that triggers the bug is not exercised by these binaries."
    },
